I would like to be able to use the Gliffy macro (or some other method) to add existing MS office drawing objects to the WIKI. I hope to use the WIKI to publish a new engineering textbook on water treatment plant design. I have a wealth of drawings that I have created in PowerPoint. I don't want to have to recreate all of those drawings in Gliffy. The drawing objects must retain their vector based format so they can be edited in the WIKI. One possible solution is to add functionality to the Gliffy macro so it can accept clipboard contents of MS office drawings. 

Image based attachments are not acceptable because they would require also saving the original drawing in some other format and would require a multiple step process for any edits to the drawing. If the wiki can only display an image file, then any revision to that display would require first editing the original drawing object file, converting the drawing to an image, and then uploading that image file to the wiki.

I rate this as a Major priority based on the suggested rating system. This is a major loss of function compared with the copy and paste functionality we have in other document creation environments.

