We don't use LDAP groups. But there is role information stored in our LDAP. For example, say we have an LDAP field called it univRole that contains a user's role on campus ( student, faculty, etc). They can be flagged as having one role, or multiple roles.
I'd like to have anyone with one of these roles in the LDAP to be added to a specific Confluence Group. If the field univRole has "student" they are added to the "confluence-students" group in Confluence. If univRole contains "student" and "employee" they are added to both "confluence-students" and "confluence-employee" groups in Confluence. The ability to select the Confluence group would need some "if-then" options.

Is there no way to map, or associate the univRole in an LDAP field, to a specific Confluence Group?

