Currently when multiple LDAP repositories have been configured with Confluence, the [Paddle|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Paddle] tool fetches results only from the first LDAP repository and exits. 
Please extend this tool to list users and groups from the second (or third or more...) repository to assist in troubleshooting external user management related problems.

The present workaround is to position/place the LDAP repository, with which the problem is being experienced, as the first repository in the {{atlassian-user.xml}} file. This will fetch results from this repository and ignore the rest.

