Default Printable Layout does not include $!settingsManager.globalSettings.customHtmlSettings.beforeHeadEnd
or any of the other CustomHTML sections. The inclusion of these would allow custom scripts and css to run and so affect content and appearance for printing.
Example Problem: An in-development math plugin uses CustomHTML-included Javascript to generate MathML on the fly - works fine in normal page views. Missing CustomHTML $!'s in Printable View means javascript is not included and math does not display properly.

